  "body": "This `curl` command:\r\n\r\n```\r\n curl -s --data '{\"method\":\"trace_block\",\"params\":[\"0x3\"],\"id\":\"1\",\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\"}' -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -X POST <RPC_URL>\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhen run against OE, returns this JSON:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"result\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"action\": {\r\n        \"author\": \"0x5088d623ba0fcf0131e0897a91734a4d83596aa0\",\r\n        \"rewardType\": \"block\",\r\n        \"value\": \"0x478eae0e571ba000\"\r\n      },\r\n      \"blockHash\": \"0x3d6122660cc824376f11ee842f83addc3525e2dd6756b9bcf0affa6aa88cf741\",\r\n      \"blockNumber\": 3,\r\n      \"result\": null,\r\n      \"subtraces\": 0,\r\n      \"traceAddress\": [],\r\n      \"transactionHash\": null,\r\n      \"transactionPosition\": null,\r\n      \"type\": \"reward\"\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"action\": {\r\n        \"author\": \"0xc8ebccc5f5689fa8659d83713341e5ad19349448\",\r\n        \"rewardType\": \"uncle\",\r\n        \"value\": \"0x340aad21b3b70000\"\r\n      },\r\n      \"blockHash\": \"0x3d6122660cc824376f11ee842f83addc3525e2dd6756b9bcf0affa6aa88cf741\",\r\n      \"blockNumber\": 3,\r\n      \"result\": null,\r\n      \"subtraces\": 0,\r\n      \"traceAddress\": [],\r\n      \"transactionHash\": null,\r\n      \"transactionPosition\": null,\r\n      \"type\": \"reward\"\r\n    }\r\n  ],\r\n  \"id\": \"1\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhich is a record of the block reward and uncle reward for the given block (block 3 which is the first block that has an uncle). \r\n\r\nTurbo Geth (on the `1109-tracing` branch) returns:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\": \"1\",\r\n  \"result\": []\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nfor the same block. \r\n\r\nThis issue simply tracks the fact that `trace_block` does not yet report rewards.\r\n\r\nNote: `trace_block` calls into `trace_filter` to get the traces for the block, but `trace_filter` does not need to retrieve block reward as OE does not report block reward from`trace_filter` (it only reports block rewards for `trace_block`). \r\n\r\nIt's an open question if we want to extend `trace_filter` to include block reward.",
